Organization Name: CITY OF FORT WORTH | HAZEL HARVEY PEACE CENTER FOR NEIGHBORHOODS | DIVERSITY & INCLUSION
Description: Provides information and services related to basic human rights, including enforcement of the city's anti-discrimination, such as Fair Housing Act and City of Fort Worth fair housing ordinance, tenant/landlord issues and fair housing rights, and Equal Employment Opportunity ordinance.

Organization Name: TARRANT COUNTY GOVERNMENT | COURTHOUSE | JUSTICE OF THE PEACE COURTS
Description: Provides courts for three different kinds of civil lawsuits up to $10,000 limit: evictions, justice civil, and small claims. They also serve as a trial court judge for Class C misdemeanors as well as an administrative court judge for a variety of miscellaneous court procedures. Also act as notaries public, hold inquests and perform marriages.
